webpackJsonp([24981828498042],{7804:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{html:'<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/papascott/394403325/" title="Photo Sharing"><img src="https://farm1.static.flickr.com/186/394403325_79ac1fce4b.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="IMG 1904" /></a></p>\n<p>Tomorrow Christopher\'s school is celebrating <a href="http://german.about.com/library/weekly/aa020501a.htm"><em>Fasching</em></a>... here are the main components of his costume. Aficionados of 20th century German children\'s literature can probably guess what will come of it.</p>\n<p>Here in northern Germany <em>Fasching</em> or <em>Karneval</em> is strictly for children, unlike in lesser developed parts of the country (although some towns near us celebrate <a href="http://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faslam"><em>Faslam</em></a>, which seems to be <em>Karneval</em> reduced to the bare essentials: getting drunk in a clown costume).</p>',fields:{title:"Fasching, the night before",date:"18 Feb 2007",url:"https://papascott.de/2007-02-18-fasching-the-night-before/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2007-02-18-fasching-the-night-before/",prev:{fields:{title:"Soundtrack of Life",date:"16 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-16-soundtrack-of-life/"}},next:{fields:{title:"Hanging Out With The Goats",date:"18 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-18-hanging-out-with-the-goats/"}}}}}});
